Diagnosis. Adult (
Fig. 9
). Wingspan 8.0−12.0 mm. This species is superficially similar to G. p i s t a (Diakonoff, 1984 ), but
G. permixtana
can be distinguished by the cornutus about 1 / 3 the length of the phallus in the male genitalia (
Fig. 18
); and the ductus bursae about 1 / 2 the length of the corpus bursae and the ductus seminalis arising from posterior 1 / 3 of the ductus bursae in the female genitalia (
Fig. 26
). In G. p i s t a , the cornutus is about 3 / 5 the length of the phallus; and the ductus bursae is slightly longer than the corpus bursae and the ductus seminalis arises from the anterior 1 / 3 of the ductus bursae.
